<shortcode>01mz</shortcode>
<problem>
                <para>What colour is the light emitted by hydrogen when an electron makes the transition from energy level 5 down to energy level 2? (Use <link target-id="fig:Henergy"/> to find the energy of the released photon.)</para>
              </problem>
              <solution url="TODO">
                  <para>
                  <latex display="block">
                  \begin{align}
                  \Delta E &amp; =  E_5 - E_2 \\
                           &amp; =  <unit_number><number><coeff>21.0</coeff><base>10</base><exp>-19</exp></number><unit>J</unit></unit_number> - <unit_number><number><coeff>16.3</coeff><base>10</base><exp>-19</exp></number><unit>J</unit></unit_number> \\
                           &amp; =  <unit_number><number><coeff>4.7</coeff><base>10</base><exp>-19</exp></number><unit>J</unit></unit_number>
                  \end{align}
                  </latex>
                  </para>
                  <para>
                  <latex display="block">
                  \begin{align}
                  \lambda &amp; =  \frac{hc}{\Delta E} \\
                          &amp; =  \frac{(<unit_number><number><coeff>6.63</coeff><base>10</base><exp>-34</exp></number><unit>m<sup>2</sup>kg·s<sup>-1</sup></unit></unit_number>)(<unit_number><number><coeff>3</coeff><base>10</base><exp>8</exp></number><unit>m·s<sup>-1</sup></unit></unit_number>)}{<unit_number><number><coeff>4.7</coeff><base>10</base><exp>-19</exp></number><unit>J</unit></unit_number>} \\ 
                          &amp; =  <unit_number><number>423</number><unit>nm</unit></unit_number>
                  \end{align}
                  </latex>
                  The colour of light emitted at <unit_number><number>423</number><unit>nm</unit></unit_number> is violet.
                  </para>
                  </solution>
                  <correct />
